        "description": "Continuum FEA with elastic-perfectly-plastic titanium alloy material model (Ti-6Al-4V, E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa) and nonlinear geometry (large displacement). Frictional contact (μ=0.2) between screw and rod. Model form justified by published literature and prior FDA validation studies. Achieved Gradation 3: model form documented with explicit justification of all constitutive assumptions."
      },
      "rationale": "The elastic-perfectly-plastic model for Ti-6Al-4V is well-established for monotonic loading to fracture and is consistent with prior FDA V&V studies for spinal implants. Large-displacement formulation is required given the 40 mm displacement target. Frictional contact coefficient μ=0.2 is supported by tribological literature for metal-on-metal titanium interfaces. Required level 3 reflects the medium model risk level; achieved level 3 confirms the model form is fully documented and justified."
