        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending condition (5° offset, 10 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature). Required level 3 would demand at least two independent test conditions (e.g., varied offset angle or loading rate). Only one condition tested; achieved level 2 documented as a known limitation. Acceptance maintained because E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs and model risk level 3 tolerates this single-condition limitation per the credibility assessment team's risk-informed judgment."
      },
      "rationale": "As documented in the COU description, testing was performed under a single ASTM F1717 condition. This limits the test conditions factor to achieved level 2, below the required level 3 for model risk level 3. The credibility assessment team accepted this limitation because: (1) ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardised condition that is directly relevant to the COU; (2) all three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96; and (3) the single-condition limitation is consistent with regulatory precedent for this device class. The shortfall is documented transparently and does not affect the overall Accepted decision."
    },
