        "description": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions, loading) verified to be equivalent to experimental test conditions by direct comparison of CMM measurements, certified material reports, and test protocol documentation. Equivalency matrix completed with all items confirmed. Achieved Gradation 3: formal equivalency matrix with documented evidence for each input parameter."
      },
      "rationale": "A formal equivalency matrix was constructed mapping each FEA input to the corresponding experimental measurement or test protocol specification. Geometry: FEA dimensions match CMM measurements within 0.05 mm. Material: FEA properties match certified lot test reports. Boundary conditions: FEA replicates ASTM F1717 fixture geometry and constraint definitions. Loading: FEA applies identical 5° offset compression. All equivalency items confirmed; required level 3 is met."
