        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Quantitative comparison metric: percent difference and E/uval ratio per ASME V&V 40 Section 6.4. Acceptance bounds: <10% difference AND E/uval < 1.96 for each QoI. Results: stiffness 4.2%/0.87; yield force 6.1%/1.27; force at 40 mm 7.8%/1.62. All three QoIs satisfy acceptance bounds. Achieved Gradation 3: quantitative metric with pre-specified bounds and validation uncertainty quantification."
      },
      "rationale": "All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance bounds (percent difference <10% and E/uval < 1.96). The E/uval metric explicitly accounts for both model prediction uncertainty and experimental measurement uncertainty, providing a statistically grounded comparison. Pre-specification of acceptance bounds before unblinding of experimental results eliminates confirmation bias. Required level 3 is met."
