        "description": "Three QoIs selected: construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. All three are directly specified by ASTM F1717 and are clinically relevant surrogates for construct fatigue life and fracture risk. QoI selection justified by clinical failure mode analysis and regulatory precedent. Achieved Gradation 3: QoIs traceable to clinical endpoints with documented justification."
      },
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the primary outputs of the ASTM F1717 test and are directly linked to clinical performance: stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force and force at 40 mm bound the fracture risk under physiological loading. QoI selection is consistent with FDA guidance on spinal implant V&V and prior published credibility assessments. Required level 3 is met."
