  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepts the FEA modeling framework for predicting ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. All 13 V&V 40 factors have been assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors achieve their required credibility level; the single exception (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted on the grounds that: (1) ASTM F1717 defines a single standardised test condition that is directly representative of the COU; (2) all three QoIs satisfy the quantitative acceptance bounds (percent difference <10% and E/uval < 1.96); (3) the shortfall is documented transparently and is consistent with regulatory precedent for Class II spinal implants. The provenance chain is complete from raw experimental data through FEA predictions to validation results. Uncertainty quantification is present for all three QoIs, with combined validation uncertainties computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 6.4. The decision is supported by the structured evidence in the hasCredibilityFactor array and the three ValidationResult objects, each with comparedAgainst, prov:wasGeneratedBy, and hasUncertaintyQuantification links. Model risk level 3 with medium model influence and medium decision consequence yields an overall credibility requirement that is satisfied by the evidence assembled in this package.",
